Git Command You should now.

1. git --version            (to get the version of git)
2. git cd                   (to change the directory)
3. git ls                   (to list all files and directories in this directory)
4. git status               (to check the file that tracked or not before we add to tracked list)
5. git add FILE_NAME        (to add file or directory to tracked list)
6. git commit -m "Message or Description to the file"(to commit the new file to repository in github)
7. git add -A               (to add all file or directory to tracked list)
8  Esc -> wq                (to exit the commit prompt when you didn't give the message -m to it)

9. git init REPOSITORY_NAME (to create a new Repository)
10. mkdir PROJECT_FOLDER    (to create a project folder inside Repository)
11. mv REPOSITORY_NAME NEW_REPOSITORY_NAME  (rename your repository name{make sure that use this command inside the repository folder}
12. rm FILE_NAME            (to remove file)
13. git config --global user.name "Nhoek Deta"
14. git config --global user.email "nhoek.deta@gmail.com"
15. git commit -a -m "MESSAGE"  (commit all change to git with a given message)
16. git branch BRANCH_NAME  (to create a new branch)
17. git branch              (list all branch)
18. git checkout BRANCH_NAME(change branch to BRANCH_NAME)